Subscription token for 12 issues of The Tickle - weekly magazine for contemporary digital art and creative writing (@inwarhol), with this special limited edition created by itsgalo (@galoandstuff) titled "SURFERS".

metadata.name: Kush Buddies #54
metadata.description:
A 1937 Generative Profile Pic Collection
Kush Buddies - Created by Markyy Mark
@MarkyyMarkNFT

A movement bringing growers and breeders together to Tezos.
Kush Buddies are a hand drawn randomly generated PFP collection all being unique in their own.

With each Buddie it will belong to 1 of 6 Terpy Genetic Heritages with over +300 possible traits. We all have there favorite terps. Which terpy heritage will your buddie belong?

Genetic Information:
Limonene - Citrus, Lemon, Orange
Humulene - Woody, Earthy
Pinene - Sharp, Sweet, Pine
Linalool - Floral, Citrus, Spice
Caryophyllene - Pepper, Wood, Spice
Myrcene - Musk, Cloves, Herbal, Citrus

"Some buddies may have very special traits I would keep them safe around special holidays for a picture."

There will be 28 Buddies Reserved. These Buddies are for future Buddie team members and special events.

Royalties:
5.80% - Kush Buddies Wallet
4.20% - Kush Buddie Bakery Wallet

Thank You for supporting just another human with some dreams. I cant wait to see everyone's minted buddies.

Share your Kush Buddies on social media with #JustGrowing and #KushBuddies. Feel free to tag us too!

Twitter: @KushBuddies
Instagram: @KushBuddiesNFT

metadata.name: EDDY #74
metadata.description:
An eddy is a circular movement of water counter to a main current. It reminds me of innovations in art, like a small countercurrent to the mainstream, surfacing new techniques and aesthetics. 

I hope that EDDY will brighten your days with its playful swirl of colors, inspired by the sea, the sky, the birds, and post-impressionist paintings.

Keyboard Controls:
[F] Fill the window.
[S] Save the current view in live mode as an image (default 1125x1500px).
[1] [2] [4] [6] Change resolution, 1.5K to 9K.
[R] Reverse course.

Made with p5js and shaders.

Created by elsif, 2022.12.

metadata.name: ZOOM (4hwf) #61
metadata.description:
"Das System lässt keine Überraschung zu. Überraschung ist Ausdruck partieller Unkenntnis. Überraschung weist auf Mangel von Wissen hin, deutet Leerstellen an. Bisher hatten sie keine Leerstellen festgestellt." — Herbert W. Franke

ZOOM explores linear scaling of pixels by zooming into a noisy framebuffer. Various zoom levels are composed one below the other, becoming a cinematic animation through iteration of the hue values of the pixels in the framebuffer.

In Gedenken an Herbert W. Franke
Kim Asendorf, 2022

metadata.name: Aluna #117
metadata.description:
Aluna is the insistence that the world is made and shaped through ideas as well as processes. The series is inspired by the human-led speciation of plants such as orchids and irises, and animals such as goldfish and betta fish - whose features are often exaggerated. Not all speciation is towards ornament - our ancestors developed foods and natural materials through years of selection and hybridization, and this is continued today helping discover new resilient forms. Our ability to imagine and reshape living organisms as well as entire ecosystems is brought into focus through climate change. 

The name Aluna is based on the philosophy of the Tairona people of Colombia, survived through present-day descendants. This Andean philosophy maintains a fundamentally different perspective about the role of humans - occupied with the imagining, enhancement, and nurturing of life.

metadata.name: The Three-Body Problem #72
metadata.description:
The Three-Body Problem refers to the difficulty in evaluating an analytical expression for an object under the influence of two massive bodies. This work shows the gravitational vector field from two such bodies. Occasionally, lines will also show curves of equipotential in this field, the centre of mass of the system, the orbital paths traced out. The system is periodic and will loop forever.

Press UP to export one second of frames, and DOWN to save an SVG from the current frame.
